  "body": "I am attempting to run truffle on Ubuntu 16.04. `npm install -g truffle` is complaining that it doesnt find python or the python environment variable. For people who dont have experience with Python even googling around, deciding between python 2 and 3, setting env variables is a bit of a stretch. If this dependency is really required it should be documented. Somehow `apt install node-gyp` solved this.\r\nThese are the complete steps that worked for me to install truffle on a blank digital ocean machine:\r\n```\r\ncurl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_6.x -o nodesource_setup.sh\r\nbash nodesource_setup.sh\r\nrm nodesource_setup.sh\r\napt-get install nodejs -y\r\nnpm install pm2 -g\r\napt-get install build-essential\r\nsudo add-apt-repository ppa:jonathonf/python-3.6\r\nsudo apt-get update\r\nsudo apt-get install python3.6\r\napt install node-gyp\r\nnpm install -g truffle\r\nnpm install -g ethereumjs-testrpc\r\ntmux\r\ntestrpc\r\n```",
